Former Chilean President Patricio Aylwin has passed away, and the American people are mourning alongside the people of Chile. Aylwin played a crucial role in peacefully restoring democracy to Chile after 17 years of military rule. His presidency helped solidify Chile's democratic institutions and his first speech as president emphasized the importance of unity and collaboration among Chileans. Aylwin's life and leadership serve as a hopeful example of the progress that can be achieved in societies transitioning to democracy.